Modifications made by Illiad (2026)
-----------------------------------

Illiad repackages Odysseus as a run-from-source native desktop application. It
does not fork the product direction; the changes are a small, surgical overlay:

- Added illiad_launcher.py: a desktop entrypoint that runs the FastAPI backend
  on a loopback daemon thread and opens a native pywebview window (no browser,
  no tray). Includes automatic port fallback when the default port is busy.
- Removed the previous launcher.py (browser + system-tray launcher) and its
  test.
- src/chroma_client.py: added an in-process "embedded" ChromaDB mode
  (PersistentClient under the per-user data dir) as the default; the original
  "http" mode is preserved for server deployments.
- Changed the default web-search provider from SearXNG to DuckDuckGo so search
  works with no API key and no external service (src/settings.py,
  services/search/core.py, src/deep_research.py).
- Service health reporting adjusted so removed services (SearXNG, ntfy) report
  as disabled rather than failed in the desktop configuration
  (src/service_health.py).
- pyproject.toml, .env.example, README.md, and docs/ updated for the desktop
  run-from-source model (no Docker, no installer).

